PrecisAcceptance of a DESIGNATION wherein the ALEXANDER BAND surrenders, for an indefinite term, all of its rights and interests in and to the oil and gas that may exist within, upon or under specific tracts of land within Alexander Indian Reserves Nos. 134 and 134A in Alberta, for the purpose of allowing the Crown to issue leases, etc., to third parties for oil and gas exploration and development.
